sentences: Jon Mueller (born 1970 in Waukesha, Wisconsin) is an American percussionist and composer, active in experimental and rock disciplines.
In 1990, he studied with jazz musician Hal Russell while attending Columbia College in Chicago.
Mueller graduated in 1995 from Cardinal Stritch University in Milwaukee with a bachelor's degree in English.
In 2008, he earned his Master of Business Administration degree.
In 2003, he began experimenting with vibrating drums on top of speakers.
The Shepherd Express, OnMilwaukee, Amoeba Records Hollywood, and contributed to The 100 Best Business Books of All Time (Penguin/Portfolio) by Jack Covert and Todd Sattersten.
